You are on the correct page. Now follow these steps exactly to execute your Salesforce practical. The uploaded PDF also shows the same procedure. 
Step-by-Step Execution
Step 1: Open Setup


Click the ⚙️ Gear Icon at the top-right


Select Setup



Step 2: Create Custom Object


In Setup search bar, type Object Manager


Open Object Manager


Click Create → Custom Object 



Step 3: Enter Object Details
Fill like this:


Label: Comment


Plural Label: Comments


Record Name: Comment Name


Data Type: Text


Tick:


✅ Allow Reports


Then click Save. 

Step 4: Create Tab


In Setup search, type Tabs


Open Tabs


Under Custom Object Tabs, click New


Now:


Select Object = Comment


Choose any icon/tab style


Click Next → Next → Save 



Step 5: Create App


Search App Manager


Open App Manager


Click New Lightning App 


Fill:


App Name = Comment Box App


Click:


Next → Next → Next



Step 6: Add Items
Move these to selected items:


Contacts


Comments


Click Next. 

Step 7: Select Profile


Select System Administrator


Move it to Selected Profiles


Click Save & Finish 



Step 8: Open Your App


Click the App Launcher (9 dots icon)


Search and open Comment Box App 



Step 9: Create Record


Open Comments


Click New


Enter any comment


Save it


Your mini project is completed successfully.
